# Settings Global Simplicity and Control™ (175)

**Docs:** `docs/navigation/175_SETTINGS_GLOBAL_SIMPLICITY_AND_CONTROL_STANDARD.md` · Checklist: `docs/navigation/174_SETTINGS_SIMPLICITY_AND_CONTRAST_LIVE_CHECKLIST.md`

## Standing rule

Every Settings experience must minimize reading, visible choices, and decision fatigue.

## Contrast

- Light surface → dark readable text (`SETTINGS_TEXT` / `settingsTokens`)
- Dark surface → light readable text
- Disabled must remain readable; selected state must not rely on color alone

## Correct controls

| Need | Control |
|------|---------|
| On/off | `SettingsToggle` |
| One of several | `SettingsDropdown` — never option card stacks |
| Range | `SettingsSlider` |
| Optional education | `SettingsHelpAccordion` (closed by default) |

Shared home: `components/companion/settings/`

## Default section structure

1. One-sentence explanation
2. Control
3. Short selected-state description
4. Optional Learn More

## Save

Show **Settings saved** · stay on page · preserve navigation origin and drafts · no auto-redirect

## Quality test

A first-time user should understand the setting, its current value, and how to change it within about ten seconds.
